1
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,208
Well, boy? Why do
you stand there crying?

2
00:00:51,958 --> 00:00:54,875
Because... the kids
at my school...

3
00:00:54,958 --> 00:00:57,208
They said I was a
murderer's son...

4
00:00:57,291 --> 00:01:02,000
And then they said, "Your whole
family fights wars for money!"

5
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:06,541
Waste of salt,
crying over the truth.

6
00:01:07,208 --> 00:01:11,250
Our men have been mercenaries
for eight generations now.

7
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:15,750
Going back to your grandpa's
grandpa's grandpa's grandpa.

8
00:01:16,416 --> 00:01:20,625
What do you think your pop
died of in Columbia? The flu?

9
00:01:20,708 --> 00:01:23,125
He knew you were on the
way and needed cash...

10
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:26,583
Bit off more than he could
chew... What's that look...?

11
00:01:26,666 --> 00:01:28,291
Didn't your mother
ever tell you?

12
00:01:28,375 --> 00:01:30,291
But... does that mean...

13
00:01:30,375 --> 00:01:32,750
you killed people,
too, Grandpa?!

14
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:36,500
Course I killed people, boy.
More than a few.

15
00:01:36,583 --> 00:01:38,166
But, what for...?

16
00:01:38,250 --> 00:01:41,791
What did they do
to deserve... that?!

17
00:01:41,875 --> 00:01:46,375
Deserve's got nothing to
do with it... It's a job...

18
00:01:46,458 --> 00:01:48,833
Anyone who found himself
at the end of my gun,

19
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:51,125
he was fighting for something.

20
00:01:51,208 --> 00:01:54,083
Bring down a government,
or prop one up.

21
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:56,000
For homeland, or someone else's.

22
00:01:56,083 --> 00:02:01,375
For family. For a woman.
Maybe just food and drink.

23
00:02:01,458 --> 00:02:06,375
So many damn reasons.
Some good... some bad.

24
00:02:06,458 --> 00:02:09,833
A mercenary doesn't
ask questions, boy...

25
00:02:09,916 --> 00:02:13,000
It's enough to know the other
man's dying for something...

26
00:02:13,083 --> 00:02:15,916
But that reason of his...
whatever it was...

27
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,958
was it really worth
fighting for...? Maybe...

28
00:02:19,041 --> 00:02:21,041
But who says you
need some epic cause

29
00:02:21,125 --> 00:02:23,708
before you can shed some blood?

30
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:26,416
Fighting for
filthy lucre's always

31
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:29,875
been good enough for me...
Pays the bills.

32
00:02:30,916 --> 00:02:35,583
Toss us a bit of coin... and
we will risk life, and limb...

33
00:02:35,666 --> 00:02:38,333
They dangle their spare
change in front of our nose,

34
00:02:38,416 --> 00:02:40,041
and we come running.

35
00:02:40,125 --> 00:02:43,541
We march onto chessboards
all over the world,

36
00:02:43,625 --> 00:02:47,916
for mere pennies.
Kill for 'em. Die for 'em.

37
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,750
But really...? It aint'
about the damn pennies.

38
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:54,166
We go because we enjoy it.

39
00:02:55,041 --> 00:02:56,458
We fight for money,
'cause fighting

40
00:02:56,541 --> 00:02:59,166
for fun's just too
horrible to admit.

41
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:02,208
Die for a dollar?
Kill for some kroner?

42
00:03:02,291 --> 00:03:06,666
Sign us up. We're the
scum of the earth, boy.

43
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:09,250
With a legacy like ours,

44
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:12,833
course they're going
to pick on you at school.

45
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:17,083
You cry, but I bet you'll come
around one of these days...

46
00:03:17,166 --> 00:03:20,041
You know, the apple doesn't
fall far from the tree.

47
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:29,375
You were right... It's never
been about the money.

48
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:32,333
It's always been about the fun.

49
00:03:32,416 --> 00:03:33,791
Hurry up! Grab
anything we can use

50
00:03:33,875 --> 00:03:36,083
to block the doors
and fall back A-SAP!

51
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:37,166
Yessir!

52
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:40,125
Get Squad Two on
the radio! Move, dammit!

53
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,750
Help! Help me!
Someone fucking help me!

54
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:14,916
Dammit, they're pouring in!

55
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,416
Keep shooting! Keep shooting!

56
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,833
Our bullets aren't doing shit!

57
00:04:17,916 --> 00:04:19,416
Fall back, now!

58
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,708
Where's the medic?!

59
00:04:20,791 --> 00:04:23,416
They flanked us--we're
totally cut off! Fuck!

60
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,125
Oh shit, oh shit, oh shit!

61
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:10,541
This is Squad Two...!

62
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:12,833
Captain, we're in
the shit down here!

63
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:19,000
We're not gonna be able
to make it back to you guys!

64
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,208
Listen, asshole...!

65
00:05:21,291 --> 00:05:23,250
I don't care if
you have to crawl...!

66
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:26,333
Fall back to the round
table room--that's an order!

67
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:28,625
This is the easiest
spot to reinforce...

68
00:05:28,708 --> 00:05:30,250
We can hold out for a while.

69
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:33,208
You have to retreat--you're
a sitting duck out there!

70
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:36,041
We're not going to close the
barricade until you're back!

71
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:38,500
Negative, Captain--no can do.

72
00:05:39,166 --> 00:05:41,916
They've torn us all
to hell, myself included.

73
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:44,625
He's dead, okay?

74
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:47,291
Cap him again before he
tries to fucking eat us.

75
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:51,041
Someone... gimmie some water...

76
00:05:51,416 --> 00:05:53,541
We'll hold them off
for as long as we can...

77
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:56,375
But you gotta close
that barricade now!

78
00:05:56,458 --> 00:05:58,333
Good hunting, Captain.

79
00:05:58,416 --> 00:06:00,125
[speaking French]

80
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:11,458
Be that way...
you brave bastard...

81
00:06:11,541 --> 00:06:13,750
If you're ready
to die, go for it.

82
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:15,208
I guess this is adieu.

83
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:16,916
Been a hell of a ride,

84
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,375
Captain--I don't
regret a thing...

85
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:20,291
Goodbye!

86
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:36,833
Let's close up the barricade.

87
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:39,750
Take this huge fucking table
and add it to the pile...

88
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:42,041
Seal that goddamn hole already!

89
00:06:42,125 --> 00:06:45,083
But, sir... what
about the others?

90
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:48,083
All KIA.

91
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,500
Understood... They'll be missed.

92
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,500
What's it matter...?!
We're all gonna die tonight!

93
00:06:55,583 --> 00:06:57,000
Shut the fuck up!

94
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:59,958
How're we supposed to
fight Nazi vampires...?!

95
00:07:00,041 --> 00:07:04,041
It's bullshit...! Integra
and Alucard sold us out!

96
00:07:04,416 --> 00:07:06,166
I'm done--I'm fucking done!

97
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:08,750
What're you yellin' about...?

98
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:12,916
There's nowhere to go...
Not that I'm letting you leave.

99
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,875
The hell you aren't...!
I'm outta here!

100
00:07:15,958 --> 00:07:19,958
Face the facts...
This place will be our grave...

101
00:07:20,041 --> 00:07:22,666
This mansion our
tombstone--our gravekeeper

102
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,833
that cast-iron bitch Integra...

103
00:07:24,916 --> 00:07:26,791
And our epitaph...?

104
00:07:26,875 --> 00:07:30,583
"Here lies the badass
Wild Geese--they kicked

105
00:07:30,666 --> 00:07:33,500
beaucoup de Nazi ass
for Queen and crumpets."

106
00:07:33,583 --> 00:07:36,583
But they won't
write any of that...

107
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,583
Thanks to you,
it's going to read...

108
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:42,125
"Here lie those gutless pussies
who died pissing themselves

109
00:07:42,208 --> 00:07:44,666
and crying like schoolgirls."

110
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,000
Man the fuck up, bitch...!

111
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:51,583
You'll die with honor if I have
to tie you to your damn post!

112
00:07:51,666 --> 00:07:53,416
You take the money
because you like it

113
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:56,250
and you fight because
you like it--and now...!

114
00:07:56,333 --> 00:08:00,208
You're going to die
like a merc and like it!

115
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:04,958
Yessir... Yeah...!
Fuck...! Fuck!

116
00:08:05,041 --> 00:08:08,583
Come on--no one ever said dying
tonight was a sure thing...

117
00:08:08,666 --> 00:08:11,208
We got a nice big barricade.

118
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:14,625
Now... get up and
come lend a hand...

119
00:08:14,708 --> 00:08:17,583
Just in case ma chere
leaves us any of 'em.

120
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:35,000
Just keep shooting! Why can't
we hit these assholes?!

121
00:08:35,958 --> 00:08:37,125
Fuck!

122
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:38,916
These sons-of-bitches
aren't slowing down any!

123
00:08:47,916 --> 00:08:49,416
Don't you die on me, man!

124
00:08:49,791 --> 00:08:51,166
I'm done--we all are.

125
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,625
Keep it together!

126
00:08:58,041 --> 00:09:02,666
That's it! Burn it down!
Kill every bastard you find!

127
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:05,583
This is the best fight
Hellsing can put up...?

128
00:09:05,666 --> 00:09:08,875
These sad meat-sacks
are your combat elite...?!

129
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:10,625
God, what a joke!

130
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:21,583
Flush 'em out.

131
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:39,333
I've got something
special for you!

132
00:10:00,541 --> 00:10:05,000
That's impossible...
I'm back home...?!

133
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:08,708
Daddy!

134
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:15,125
I'm so glad you're home, Daddy.

135
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:21,958
M-Michelle...? It's not...
You're not my daughter...

136
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:25,125
She's dead...
You're not Michelle...!

137
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:27,833
Why do you look like her?!

138
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:31,375
Why do I look like who...?
What's wrong, Daddy?

139
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:34,375
You're not real...
You're not real...!

140
00:10:37,416 --> 00:10:38,875
Oh, God...

141
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:41,458
You're another illusion...

142
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:47,333
You can't be standing here...

143
00:10:47,416 --> 00:10:51,833
but God, you look just
like her! Oh, Michelle...!

144
00:10:51,916 --> 00:10:54,000
Daddy has missed you so much!

145
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:57,375
Joke's on you, Daddy!

146
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:05,416
She's worm-food...
and so are you!

147
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:08,375
Sorry I had to cut
your reunion short!

148
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:14,041
All right, Sergeant,
what about that one?

149
00:11:14,125 --> 00:11:16,833
Another? Give me a second, ja?

150
00:11:17,916 --> 00:11:22,416
It's pretty sour... I'm
guessing... A-negative...!

151
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,375
So? Did I get
it right this time?

152
00:11:26,125 --> 00:11:27,833
That's amazing, sir!

153
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:29,458
You're quite the
blood connoisseur...

154
00:11:29,541 --> 00:11:31,375
It's like he told you himself!

155
00:11:31,458 --> 00:11:34,041
It has a certain...
"pungent" plate.

156
00:11:34,125 --> 00:11:36,458
Such distinctions
are wasted on me.

157
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:39,208
Negative has more bite...

158
00:11:39,291 --> 00:11:42,416
And, type-A has a certain
bouquet that I really...

159
00:12:34,375 --> 00:12:36,916
I'll... make those bastards pay.

160
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:42,041
Every last... one of 'em...
will fucking die!

161
00:12:42,125 --> 00:12:44,041
I'll tear them to shreds!

162
00:12:56,916 --> 00:12:58,166
Fuck! Fuck!

163
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,916
Sons of bitches...
they got us good...!

164
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:05,208
We're losing him...! Come on!

165
00:13:05,291 --> 00:13:08,125
Dammit...! Throw chairs
onto the pile...! All of 'em!

166
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:09,541
Hurry it up, guys...!

167
00:13:09,625 --> 00:13:11,875
The barricade's
not gonna hold for long!

168
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,750
You want some, assholes?!

169
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:16,583
You idiot...!
Get down from there!

170
00:13:22,166 --> 00:13:24,208
Fuck...!

171
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:30,541
God... We're all
gonna die here...!

172
00:13:30,625 --> 00:13:33,208
Shut up! Keep that
shit to yourself!

173
00:13:33,291 --> 00:13:34,541
Even if we surrender,

174
00:13:34,625 --> 00:13:36,333
they're just gonna torture
the shit out of us...

175
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:39,791
Then they're gonna eat us
alive... It's fucking over...

176
00:13:39,875 --> 00:13:42,250
Whatever ammo's left,
hand it out!

177
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:44,458
Here, Captain...

178
00:13:44,541 --> 00:13:46,875
This is it... We're out
of silver bullets...

179
00:13:46,958 --> 00:13:49,375
Damn near out of
regular ones, too.

180
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:50,583
Come on, kill me...

181
00:13:50,666 --> 00:13:52,583
I can't even shoot
a gun anymore--

182
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:54,625
they blew out my fucking eyes!

183
00:13:55,416 --> 00:13:57,458
I take it back, sir--I
didn't mean it...!

184
00:13:57,541 --> 00:13:58,750
I don't wanna die!

185
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:00,916
Good--we're in agreement.

186
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,875
Now stop yelling in my damn ear.

187
00:14:11,416 --> 00:14:12,500
'Member that time...?

188
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:14,041
That airfield in Uganda...?

189
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:15,708
Fuckers had us pinned down...

190
00:14:15,791 --> 00:14:18,625
I thought our asses
were done for...

191
00:14:18,708 --> 00:14:20,833
And then the cavalry
came riding in...

192
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:24,500
Somehow, I don't see
that happening this time.

193
00:14:24,583 --> 00:14:26,333
Don't give up just yet...

194
00:14:26,416 --> 00:14:30,625
Seras is coming... I'm sure
of it. Bet my life on it.

195
00:14:39,875 --> 00:14:42,375
I'm getting damn sick
of those rockets...

196
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,791
How many more until
they run out, huh?

197
00:14:50,708 --> 00:14:52,333
Damage report--now...!

198
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:53,875
How many wounded?

199
00:14:53,958 --> 00:14:55,250
What are we looking at?!

200
00:14:59,791 --> 00:15:00,750
No...!

201
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:06,458
Stay with me...!
Don't you fucking die!

202
00:15:08,708 --> 00:15:10,291
Oh, God... I'm exhausted...

203
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:12,833
I'm just gonna close my eyes...

204
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:20,833
Go on... You've earned it...
I'll see ya soon.

205
00:15:28,708 --> 00:15:31,500
A direct hit, Lieutenant.
Do we advance?

206
00:15:31,583 --> 00:15:32,666
Not just yet.

207
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:35,166
Let's soften them up a bit more.

208
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:37,291
This is our last
Panzerfaust, Lieutanant.

209
00:15:37,375 --> 00:15:39,041
It's our trump card.

210
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:40,625
I could care less...!

211
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:42,500
You take that Panzerfaust...

212
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:46,333
and you launch it straight
up their mercenary asses!

213
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:49,250
Jawohl.

214
00:15:58,833 --> 00:15:59,875
What're they waiting for?

215
00:16:11,458 --> 00:16:12,583
Schiess los!

216
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:35,875
It's the bitch who
downed my zeppelin...!

217
00:16:35,958 --> 00:16:37,041
You're dead!

218
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:42,000
Captain...?

219
00:16:44,375 --> 00:16:47,541
Of course she's here--I
told you she'd come...

220
00:16:50,458 --> 00:16:53,833
Ma chere is
reporting for duty...

221
00:16:53,916 --> 00:16:56,666
Might as well smoke 'em
if you got 'em, ladies...

222
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:59,125
Time for the main event!

223
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:02,250
God, she's perfect,
isn't she...?

224
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,750
I should have kissed her
when I had the chance...

225
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,833
You're a damn fool,
Pip Bernadotte.

226
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:25,750
Outta rounds...?

227
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:27,500
Or are you surrendering?

228
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:30,375
Tough talk from
the only Nazi left!

229
00:17:31,625 --> 00:17:35,125
Trust me, you'll love this!

230
00:17:46,916 --> 00:17:48,875
This... this isn't real...!

231
00:17:48,958 --> 00:17:51,916
It's just an illusion...
It isn't real...!

232
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,875
It's not reaaaaaaaal!

233
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:59,625
Don't tell me that Seras girl
has been acting up yet again.

234
00:17:59,708 --> 00:18:00,625
Afraid so.

235
00:18:00,708 --> 00:18:01,833
She hit one of the boys

236
00:18:01,916 --> 00:18:04,208
with a rock for taking
a toy away from her.

237
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:08,500
Just a memory...!
That's all it is...!

238
00:18:08,583 --> 00:18:11,041
The teachers all say it's
like talking to a wall.

239
00:18:11,125 --> 00:18:14,625
Probably still traumatized
from, well, you know...

240
00:18:14,708 --> 00:18:18,250
Yes... but if she doesn't start
getting along with others...

241
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:22,583
I'll happily send her packing
for the good of the orphanage.

242
00:18:23,041 --> 00:18:25,083
I'm not going to break.

243
00:18:25,166 --> 00:18:28,333
I want more.

244
00:18:30,458 --> 00:18:32,708
That's all very noble,
but, well...

245
00:18:32,791 --> 00:18:36,083
isn't there anything
you'd rather do?

246
00:18:36,166 --> 00:18:37,375
No.

247
00:18:37,458 --> 00:18:40,458
At least pretend
to think it over.

248
00:18:40,541 --> 00:18:42,750
Your father was a fine
policeman--one of the best.

249
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:45,958
